node.text:
Would you dare? 🦈 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @tripfever

When “all the sharks align” and you know you’re in the right place at the right time and years and years of work and experience all come together for an opportunity to experience the very best wildlife experience @nature can offer. 

 Diver: @oceanramsey
📽 @juansharks Edited by @jarebutter
@oneoceandiving

Magical moments in the deep blue with “Grandma Great White” My great-grandmother used to swim off the south shore of Oahu everyday till she died, “Grandma great white” featured here is actually larger than “Deep Blue” who was around the day before this footage. I’ve been swimming with sharks my whole life and working professionally with them for almost 20 yrs. There’s a challenge I have in my efforts to find a balance between helping people to overcome their fear of sharks that often stems from fictitious media, and instilling a healthy level of respect for sharks. I reached the decision, long ago, to devote the rest of my life to conservation, research, and education. I hope my efforts inspire action for conservation and compassion for heavily misunderstood apex predators and other important marine life. I also hope that it means that more beautiful sharks like this will be saved from wasteful finning for sharks fin soup, shark fishing, or other wasteful things like shark nets, bycatch from industrial longline fleets, or even the pharmaceutical and souvenir trade.

node.text:
Why have pets when you can train wild macaws 🦜 We can promote your photos in our account. Check the link in our bio for instructions: @tripfever

Come every morning for food. In Spanish macaws are called guacamayas, these are native to Caracas Venezuela.

📽 TT bbitoslove
📍 Caracas, Venezuela
